Patch summary:
Add minimal desktop SELinux policy for expected VM behavior. The policy quiets
known benign denials from optional services and legacy probes, and allows
shell-driven display-density checks used by host-side desktop testing.

This patch does not broaden app privileges for normal desktop use; it documents
and permits only the small set of behaviors the VM is expected to perform.

diff --git a/private/lineage_desktop.te b/private/lineage_desktop.te
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..a3500ff34
--- /dev/null
+++ b/private/lineage_desktop.te
@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@
+# Desktop builds intentionally keep optional stats bootstrap and legacy app probes
+# denied; avoid noisy AVCs without granting the underlying access.
+dontaudit domain statsbootstrap_service:service_manager find;
+dontaudit untrusted_app_all self:netlink_route_socket nlmsg_readpriv;
+dontaudit untrusted_app_all mnt_sdcard_file:lnk_file read;
+
+# Host-driven tests query the Cuttlefish density property through shell tools.
+get_prop(shell, qemu_sf_lcd_density_prop)
